comments.body:
You can dismiss the toast manually within the action handler:

```tsx
const id = toast.success('Some information', {
  action: {
    label: 'Acknowledge',
    onClick: () => {
      toast.dismiss(id);
    },
  },
});
```

body:
I would like to be able to pass `variant` without having to call a separate function (for wrapping purposes)

```js
toast({title: 'Are you sure?', variant: 'warning', position: 'bottom-center'})
// instead of
toast.warning('Are you sure?', { position: 'bottom-center' })
```

both work but ts is yelling at the first 

looks like this is the culprit 

```ts
type ExternalToast = Omit<
  ToastProps,
  'id' | 'type' | 'title' | 'jsx' | 'promise' | 'variant'
> & {
  id?: string | number;
};
```

